{
  "operator": "sim",
  "circuit": "sim_demo",
  "title": "Truth-table simulation on machine words",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "32 patterns per machine word, propagated bitwise",
      "narrative": "Resub, fraig, and dch all need to ask &quot;do these two nodes compute the same function?&quot; quickly. ABC's answer: simulate every node on the same set of input patterns packed 32-per-word, then hash on the resulting bitvector. Two nodes with different signatures are <em>guaranteed</em> different; two with the same signature are equivalence <em>candidates</em> (a real proof needs SAT).<br><br>The cone on the left implements <code>f = x0·x1 + x0·x3 + x2·x3</code> as five fanin-2 ANDs (dashed edges = inverted). We'll fill in each node's 32-bit sim signature step by step.",
      "highlights": {
        "node-t1":   ["dimmed"],
        "node-t2":   ["dimmed"],
        "node-t3":   ["dimmed"],
        "node-n12":  ["dimmed"],
        "node-n123": ["dimmed"]
      },
      "textReplace": {
        "node-x0":   "x0\n—",
        "node-x1":   "x1\n—",
        "node-x2":   "x2\n—",
        "node-x3":   "x3\n—",
        "node-t1":   "t1\n—",
        "node-t2":   "t2\n—",
        "node-t3":   "t3\n—",
        "node-n12":  "n12\n—",
        "node-n123": "n123\n—",
        "node-f":    "f\n—"
      },
      "panes": [
        {
          "type": "kv",
          "title": "Storage per node",
          "entries": {
            "Per-node":   "<code>nWords</code> × 32-bit unsigned",
            "Default":    "<code>nWords</code> = 1 (32 patterns); 8 in dch (256 patterns)",
            "Allocation": "fixed pool, one slot per AIG object"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Seed the four PIs with standard input columns",
      "narrative": "For a 4-input cone, 32 patterns is enough to evaluate <em>every</em> input combination twice (16 patterns × 2). ABC seeds the inputs with these standard hex constants — read each row left-to-right as <strong>MSB-first</strong>, so bit i of the column corresponds to input pattern i: <code>x_k = bit k of i</code>, for k = 0..3.",
      "highlights": {
        "node-x0": ["cut-leaf"],
        "node-x1": ["cut-leaf"],
        "node-x2": ["cut-leaf"],
        "node-x3": ["cut-leaf"],
        "node-t1":   ["dimmed"],
        "node-t2":   ["dimmed"],
        "node-t3":   ["dimmed"],
        "node-n12":  ["dimmed"],
        "node-n123": ["dimmed"]
      },
      "textReplace": {
        "node-x0":   "x0\nAAAAAAAA",
        "node-x1":   "x1\nCCCCCCCC",
        "node-x2":   "x2\nF0F0F0F0",
        "node-x3":   "x3\nFF00FF00",
        "node-t1":   "t1\n—",
        "node-t2":   "t2\n—",
        "node-t3":   "t3\n—",
        "node-n12":  "n12\n—",
        "node-n123": "n123\n—",
        "node-f":    "f\n—"
      },
      "panes": [
        {
          "type": "bitvec",
          "title": "sim(x0) = 0xAAAAAAAA — bit i = (i mod 2)",
          "bits": "10101010101010101010101010101010"
        },
        {
          "type": "bitvec",
          "title": "sim(x1) = 0xCCCCCCCC — bit i = ((i&gt;&gt;1) mod 2)",
          "bits": "11001100110011001100110011001100"
        },
        {
          "type": "bitvec",
          "title": "sim(x2) = 0xF0F0F0F0 — bit i = ((i&gt;&gt;2) mod 2)",
          "bits": "11110000111100001111000011110000"
        },
        {
          "type": "bitvec",
          "title": "sim(x3) = 0xFF00FF00 — bit i = ((i&gt;&gt;3) mod 2)",
          "bits": "11111111000000001111111100000000"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "body": "<strong>Bit 0</strong> (rightmost) = pattern 0 (all inputs 0). All four columns end in 0 — correct. <strong>Bit 3</strong> (4th from right) = pattern 3 (x0=1, x1=1, x2=0, x3=0) — confirms."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Level 1: bitwise AND through t1, t2, t3",
      "narrative": "<code>sim(z) = sim(p0) AND sim(p1)</code>. One 32-bit machine instruction per node — extremely cheap. After one pass over level 1, the three primary ANDs carry their 32-bit signatures.",
      "highlights": {
        "node-x0": ["cut-leaf"],
        "node-x1": ["cut-leaf"],
        "node-x2": ["cut-leaf"],
        "node-x3": ["cut-leaf"],
        "node-t1": ["considering"],
        "node-t2": ["considering"],
        "node-t3": ["considering"],
        "node-n12":  ["dimmed"],
        "node-n123": ["dimmed"],
        "edge-x0-t1": ["active"],
        "edge-x1-t1": ["active"],
        "edge-x0-t2": ["active"],
        "edge-x3-t2": ["active"],
        "edge-x2-t3": ["active"],
        "edge-x3-t3": ["active"]
      },
      "textReplace": {
        "node-x0":   "x0\nAAAAAAAA",
        "node-x1":   "x1\nCCCCCCCC",
        "node-x2":   "x2\nF0F0F0F0",
        "node-x3":   "x3\nFF00FF00",
        "node-t1":   "t1\n88888888",
        "node-t2":   "t2\nAA00AA00",
        "node-t3":   "t3\nF000F000",
