    {
      "title": "Level 2: n12 = ¬t1 · ¬t2 — negation lives on the input",
      "narrative": "Both fanin edges into n12 are dashed → both inputs are negated. Implementation: bitwise-NOT the fanin's sim word before ANDing. <code>sim(n12) = ~sim(t1) AND ~sim(t2)</code>. Edge polarity is read locally at each AND — no separate &quot;inverter&quot; nodes exist in the AIG.",
      "highlights": {
        "node-x0": ["dimmed"],
        "node-x1": ["dimmed"],
        "node-x2": ["dimmed"],
        "node-x3": ["dimmed"],
        "node-t1":  ["cut-leaf"],
        "node-t2":  ["cut-leaf"],
        "node-t3":  ["dimmed"],
        "node-n12": ["considering"],
        "node-n123": ["dimmed"],
        "edge-t1-n12": ["active"],
        "edge-t2-n12": ["active"]
      },
      "textReplace": {
        "node-x0":   "x0\nAAAAAAAA",
        "node-x1":   "x1\nCCCCCCCC",
        "node-x2":   "x2\nF0F0F0F0",
        "node-x3":   "x3\nFF00FF00",
        "node-t1":   "t1\n88888888",
        "node-t2":   "t2\nAA00AA00",
        "node-t3":   "t3\nF000F000",
        "node-n12":  "n12\n55775577",
        "node-n123": "n123\n—",
        "node-f":    "f\n—"
      },
      "panes": [
        {
          "type": "bitvec",
          "title": "~sim(t1) = ~0x88888888 = 0x77777777",
          "bits": "01110111011101110111011101110111"
        },
        {
          "type": "bitvec",
          "title": "~sim(t2) = ~0xAA00AA00 = 0x55FF55FF",
          "bits": "01010101111111110101010111111111"
        },
        {
          "type": "bitvec",
          "title": "sim(n12) = 0x77777777 &amp; 0x55FF55FF = 0x55775577",
          "bits": "01010101011101110101010101110111"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Top: n123 then f — the 32-bit signature is the truth table",
      "narrative": "<code>sim(n123) = sim(n12) AND ~sim(t3)</code>. The output edge is dashed, so f's sim is just <code>~sim(n123)</code>.<br><br>Notice <code>0xFA88FA88</code> is <code>0xFA88</code> repeated twice — exactly the 16-bit truth table of f, evaluated once over patterns 0..15 and again over 16..31. For ≤ 4 inputs, one 32-bit word literally <em>is</em> the truth table (with redundancy).",
      "highlights": {
        "node-x0": ["dimmed"],
        "node-x1": ["dimmed"],
        "node-x2": ["dimmed"],
        "node-x3": ["dimmed"],
        "node-t1": ["dimmed"],
