    {
      "title": "Equal sim() → equivalence candidates",
      "narrative": "Resub bucket-hashes every node's signature (with polarity normalized so a value and its complement collide). When a target arrives, hash and look in the bucket — any match is a candidate equivalence. Either it really is equivalent (then ABC may merge or substitute), or it agrees on these 32 patterns but disagrees on some unrepresented pattern (a <em>spurious</em> hit, only possible when nLeavesMax ≥ 6 — for 4 inputs the 32 patterns exhaust the input space, so any match here is real).",
      "highlights": {
        "node-n123": ["considering"],
        "node-f":    ["considering"],
        "edge-n123-f": ["active"]
      },
      "textReplace": {
        "node-x0":   "x0\nAAAAAAAA",
